verbLexeme: 1. Of the sun, to go below the horizon. English = set.
nominalLexeme: 1. The time in the evening when the sky grows dark and then the sun disappears below the horizon. English = sunset.
2. The colours and light that you see in the western part of the sky when the sun disappears in the evening. English = sunset.
oldEntry: Popular explanation: an orb setting below the horizon.
